Sentencas: Perovskite-type oxides BaxSr1-xCo0.9Nb0.1O3-delta (BSCNx, x = 0.0-0.8) were synthesized and investigated as cathodes for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and electrochemical performances of Ba-doped SrCo0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathodes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Ba doping improves chemical compatibility between BSCNx oxides and Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (GDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and electrochemical performances of Ba-doped SrCo0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathodes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Effects of Ba doping on electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and electrochemical performances were systematically elucidated and discussed.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and electrochemical performances of Ba-doped SrCo0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathodes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Both thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) and polarization resistance (R-p) decrease with increasing Ba doping level up to x = 0.6, attain a minimum at x = 0.6 and then increase with further increasing x > 0.6.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and electrochemical performances of Ba-doped SrCo0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathodes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The decrease of TEC with the incorporation of Ba can be attributed to the weakened chemical expansion and the decrease of R-p with Ba is due to the increase of oxygen vacancy concentration and oxygen vacancy diffusion coefficient.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and electrochemical performances of Ba-doped SrCo0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathodes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: With a 300 mu m-thick GDC as electrolyte and BSCN0.6 as the cathode, the maximum power density of a single-cell achieves 778 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and electrochemical performances of Ba-doped SrCo0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathodes for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: All these results indicate that the BSCN0.6 oxide is a promising cathode material for IT-SOFC.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and electrochemical performances of Ba-doped SrCo0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathodes for IT-SOFCs
